This paper deals with pairwise comparisons, which are often used in decision-making and optimization problems. This suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses inconsistency indices, which are used to measure the deviation from consistency in pairwise comparisons. This could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories, which often deal with measuring and analyzing data. Finally, the paper presents an axiomatically characterized inconsistency ranking, which could be relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category, which deals with the theoretical foundations of computer science.
